						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the east wall of the compound of the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>Bijjaḷa, 1161 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the 6th regnal year of the king, Vishu, Bhādrapada ba. 1, Tuesday, corresponding to 1161 A.D., September 12.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of income derived from taxes to the god Kalidēva, by the <hi rend="italic">Ayyāvoḷe</hi> community, the <hi rend="italic">Nakharas</hi> and others of Maṇiṅgavaḷḷi. It also registers a gift made earlier during the reign of the Chālukya king Perma-Jagadēkamalla.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Epigraphia Indica.,</hi> Vol. V, pp. 9 ff.</p>						

						</summary>
